casebody.data:
January 31, 1966. No. 18,

Original.

Illinois v. Missouri. William O. Clark, Attorney General of Illinois, Richard A. Michael, Assistant Attorney General, and Terence F. MacCarthy, Special Assistant Attorney General, for plaintiff. [For earlier orders herein, see 379 U. S. 952; 380 U. S. 901, 969; ante, p. 803.]

The amended complaint is filed and the State of Missouri is allotted 60 days to answer the complaint, as amended.
